Patch Set 7: Code-Review+2

I heard that the gate seems to be OK now even without this change being merged, but it's probably only a matter of time before we hit whatever weird concatenation of circumstances was causing the failure.  So we should probably merge this to address the problem short-term.
Patch Set 7: Workflow-1

Patch Set 7:

I thought about this some more and I feel that this weirdness of something that was already merged, failing later and then passing again at the gate should probably not be letting us skip our tests. I think we should figure out and fix this weird behavior at the gate with these 2 tests specifically which was causing the FakeStoreApi to be ignored, before we decide to remove 2 otherwise meaningful tests that were added to support their respective code changes.

Patch Set 7: Workflow+1 Code-Review+2

Dharini, I agree with your concerns, but this is a *temporary* measure to stabilize the gate.

At this point in the cycle, we can't waste time (or donated resources) rechecking important patches upwards of 4 or 5 times because of these two flakey tests.

Patch Set 7:

@Dharini: I want to be clear about this.  This is a short term fix to get the gate un-blocked.  The tests have to be fixed, which hopefully would include understanding the weird behavior, but could include replacing them with different tests that give the original patch appropriate coverage.  I was serious about reverting the original patch if we don't have a follow-up patch that provides appropriate test coverage.

Patch Set 7:

@Dharini: the above came out harsher than I meant.  I should have prefaced it with "Your concerns about skipping the tests are well placed, but don't worry about this patch because we are definitely going to follow up."

Patch Set 7: -Workflow

Agreeing with Brian and Ian at the moment and removing workflow -1 as this is just a "temporary" way of getting way with gate failures and these tests will be worked on and added soon after.

Doesn't show up in the zuul queue ATM, so giving a +A to nudge it.
